<H3 align="justify", style="margin-left:60px;margin-right:60px;">Presentation</H3>
<p align="justify", style="margin-left:60px;margin-right:60px;">
Nowadays, there is a significant demand for computational chemists with knowledge of 
artificial intelligence, data science, automation and cheminformatics. The proposed workshop aims to address this 
demand and provide the new generations of computational chemists with the necessary 
knowledge on these topics.<br> <br>
<H3 align="justify", style="margin-left:60px;margin-right:60px;">Description</H3>
<p align="justify", style="margin-left:60px;margin-right:60px;">
In its second edition, this workshop combines the basics of machine learning, data science and cheminformatics with the most 
relevant cutting-edge examples in these fields. The topics covered were especially 
chosen for computational chemists aiming to learn about these subjects.<br> <br>
<H3 align="justify", style="margin-left:60px;margin-right:60px;">Target audience</H3>
<p align="justify", style="margin-left:60px;margin-right:60px;">
This workshop is aimed at MSc/PhD students, postdoctoral researchers, and university 
professors with prior experience in computational chemistry who are interested in learning or 
expanding their knowledge of machine learning, data science, automation, and cheminformatics. Participants are 
recommended to have basic knowledge of programming or experience with Linux. Additionally, attendees must have 
a good command of English.<br> <br>
<H3 align="justify", style="margin-left:60px;margin-right:60px;">Course format</H3>
<p align="justify", style="margin-left:60px;margin-right:60px;">
The program will be delivered in-person through content-based and hands-on sessions.<br> <br>
<H3 align="justify", style="margin-left:60px;margin-right:60px;">Workshop certificate</H3>
<p align="justify", style="margin-left:60px;margin-right:60px;">
Attendees who fully participate and attend each session will receive a workshop certificate accredited by CSIC. <br> <br>
